(81, 1, '2016-03-30 05:31:55', '2016-03-30 05:31:55', '<p class=\"justify\">Axelle is a third year student in European Law at Maastricht University. Next year, she will be doing a Master in Globalisation and Human Rights at the same University. Her strong interest in human rights developed from the fact that not a day goes by without she -like everybody else- hears about various fundamental rights violations taking place throughout the world. Her home country -Belgium- is also concerned. She does not value success at the cost of others and this constitutes one of the reasons why she only sees herself work in the field of human rights later on. She wants to see those situations of violation redressed, and deeply believes in the potential of the Human Rights Litigation Foundation to effectively contribute to this objective.</p>', 'Axelle Delcuve', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-axelle-delcuve', '', '', '2017-07-26 09:39:06', '2017-07-26 09:39:06', '', 0, 'http://themes.webinane.com/dummy/lifeline_1/?post_type=dict_team&#038;p=81', 0, 'dict_team', '', 0),
(82, 1, '2016-03-30 05:31:57', '2016-03-30 05:31:57', '<p class=\"justify\">Zouhaier is the founder of Just Rights law firm and the President of the HRL Foundation. Holding a Master’s degree in Criminal Law from the Vrije Universiteit Brussel (V.U.B.), he has been a lawyer at the Brussels Bar since 2007. Already in his second year as a lawyer trainee, he defended his first case before the ECtHR, Grand Chamber – M.S.S. vs. Belgium, Greece 21-01-2011. The Court’s decision he obtained forever changed the application of article 3 of the ECHR and the blind application of the principle of legitimate expectation between Member States of the Council of Europe. Today he is worthy of the name of Human Rights lawyer, having obtained a record of sentences against States, in a limited time. His knowledge of the law and human rights as well as his mathematically logic approach grant him the capacity to offer a solution even in the most complex cases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"justify\">He has noticed that a huge amount of victims do not have access to justice due to many barriers (for example: lack of expertise, financial barriers, political barriers, etc.) which render access to Court difficult or even impossible, not only for the victims themselves but also for human rights defenders, to such extent that he even considered giving up his fight for justice. It follows that, as the Committee for the Prevention of Torture (CPT) Reports demonstrate, many European States persist to commit gross violations of vulnerable people’s rights with absolute impunity. Instead of ending his career, he rather decided to help the victims of the most flagrant violations in Europe and to devote voluntarily some of his time to create and manage a foundation whose aim is to set up diverse programmes to fight proactively against human rights violations committed by States. He is convinced that bringing actors such as NGOs, national lawyers, human rights lawyers, etc. together in the national and European level will permit to fight against existing gross human rights violations more effectively. He strongly believes that the Foundation will occupy its rightful place along with other big organizations such as Amnesty International or Human Rights Watch in that it would consist in their continuation, by fighting in front of international jurisdictions every gross violation reported by those organizations. Zouhaier Chihaoui believes the time has come to launch the Foundation, and is only waiting for your support to be able to contribute together to this revolt against European States’ impunity which could, at some point, affect us all</p>', 'Zouhaier Chihaoui', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1-adv-zouhaier-chihaoui', '', '', '2017-05-01 05:57:09', '2017-05-01 05:57:09', '', 0, 'http://themes.webinane.com/dummy/lifeline_1/?post_type=dict_team&#038;p=82', 0, 'dict_team', '', 0),
