(270, 1, '2017-03-21 14:55:17', '2017-03-21 14:55:17', '<p class=\"justify\">Zouhaier Chihaoui is a human rights lawyer practicing in Belgium. He has up to this day conducted numerous procedures before the European Court of Human Rights, after realizing that gross violations committed by the Belgian State were often tolerated at national level. On the basis of his experience in this field, he considers more and more the European Court of Human Rights as the one and only jurisdiction capable of effectively protecting vulnerable victims against the acts committed by European States. Nevertheless, .</p>\n\n<p class=\"justify\">He has noticed that a huge amount of victims do not have access to justice due to many barriers (for example: lack of expertise, financial barriers, political barriers, etc.) which render access to Court difficult or even impossible, not only for the victims themselves but also for human rights defenders, to such extent that he even considered giving up his fight for justice. It follows that, as the Committee for the Prevention of Torture (CPT) Reports demonstrate, many European States persist to commit gross violations of vulnerable people’s rights with absolute impunity. Instead of ending his career, he rather decided to help the victims of the most flagrant violations in Europe and to devote voluntarily some of his time to create and manage a foundation whose aim is to set up diverse programmes to fight proactively against human rights violations committed by States. He is convinced that bringing actors such as NGOs, national lawyers, human rights lawyers, etc. together in the national and European level will permit to fight against existing gross human rights violations more effectively. He strongly believes that the Foundation will occupy its rightful place along with other big organizations such as Amnesty International or Human Rights Watch in that it would consist in their continuation, by fighting in front of international jurisdictions every gross violation reported by those organizations. Zouhaier Chihaoui believes the time has come to launch the Foundation, and is only waiting for your support to be able to contribute together to this revolt against European States’ impunity which could, at some point, affect us all</p>', 'Adv. Zouhaier Chihaoui', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-21 14:55:17', '2017-03-21 14:55:17', '', 82, 'http://localhost/hrlfoundation/2017/03/18/82-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
