(282, 1, '2017-03-18 08:15:14', '2017-03-18 08:15:14', '<p class=\"justify\">Léa Van Hoorde is a third-year European and International law student at the Catholic University of Lille, on the campus in Paris. Léa has always been really interested and implicated about the protection of Human Rights, because they are fundamental and basic rights that belong to every person in our world. She started working with the team in July and she strongly believes in the HRL foundation project. Litigation is essential and necessary to protect and improve the protection of the rights and freedoms in our world today.</p>', 'Léa van Hoorde', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lea-van-hoorde', '', '', '2017-04-01 10:42:26', '2017-04-01 10:42:26', '', 0, 'http://localhost/hrlfoundation/?post_type=dict_team&#038;p=282', 0, 'dict_team', '', 0);
