=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Raise funds through donations, sponsoring, and crowdfunding for the promotion of human rights litigation at national and international level;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=\"10px\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Promote human rights litigation at national level by way of working with and supporting NGOs with similar objectives as the HRL Foundation;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=\"10px\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Promote collaboration between Human Rights actors across Europe;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=\"30px\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Promote access to justice for vulnerable groups of people, such as ethnic minorities, children, immigrants including asylum seekers, LGBTs, people with disabilities, detainees, the mentally or physically ill, and more;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Promote litigation before institutions such as the European Court of Human Rights, and promote compliance with the judgment of these Courts;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=\"10px\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Promote access to justice for victims of gross human rights violations without the financial means to go to Court;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=\"40px\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Protect and support human rights activists and defenders around the world;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_empty_space height=\"25px\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"objective\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"objective\">Promote education and training of human rights activists and defenders around the world;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row col_title=\"<strong>Recent</strong> News\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\" heading_style=\"sec-heading\" col_title=\"<strong>Recent</strong> News\"][sh_recent_news number=\"6\" category=\"News\" margins=\"top\" title=\"Recent News\" heading_style=\"simple\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\" heading_style=\"sec-heading\" col_title=\"<strong>Our</strong> Projects\"][sh_welfare_projects number=\"6\" category=\"project\" sort_by=\"0\" sorting_order=\"DESC\"][vc_empty_space][vc_separator color=\"black\" el_class=\"space-top\"][vc_row_inner el_class=\"space-top1\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p class=\"justify\">Scan your Code here</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[qrcode]</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row parallax=\"true\" pattren=\"1\" top_margin=\"1\" parallax_bg=\"227\"][vc_column][sh_ceo_message number=\"6\" overlap=\"true\" cat=\"testimonials\" sort_by=\"0\" sorting_order=\"ASC\" category=\"38\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-05 06:25:10', '2017-04-05 06:25:10', '', 95, 'https://hrlfoundation.org/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(571, 1, '2017-04-05 06:31:21', '2017-04-05 06:31:21', '[vc_row top_margin=\"1\" bottom_margin=\"1\"][vc_column][rev_slider_vc alias=\"lifeline 2\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row content_placement=\"middle\" el_class=\"first-background\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Why a Human Rights Litigation Foundation?\" font_container=\"tag:h1|font_size:20|text_align:center|color:%23000000\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Istok%20Web%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\"][vc_empty_space height=\"20px\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p class=\"justify\">The world is currently facing a global human rights crisis and is confronted with tremendous challenges. Human rights violations and abuses are on the rise in every region of the world: arbitrary detention and intimidation of opposition leaders in Venezuela; domestic violence in India; arbitrary detention and intimidation of lawyers and activists in China; death sentences carried out after unfair trials in Iran; excessive use of force by security forces in Egypt; killings, torture, enforced disappearances and mass arbitrary arrests in Burundi; abusive homophobic laws and attacks on LGBTs in Russia; increasing human rights violations in Turkey since the attempted coup last July; inadequate material conditions in immigration detention centres and ill-treatment of asylum seekers in Bulgaria; police violence towards prisoners, ethnic minorities and asylum seekers in various European States; arbitrary child detention in Greece and Hungary; arbitrary detention of asylum seekers in Belgium and in the Netherlands,... This list unfortunately goes on and on.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p class=\"justify\">Let us also not forget the dangerous rise of populist leaders in the world, which constitutes a serious threat to human rights.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p class=\"justify\">In addition to this overall context, there is something more at stake today