(737, 1, '2017-07-26 09:47:25', '2017-07-26 09:47:25', '<p class=\"justify\">Martina Guarracino holds a Masters degree in Law from Pisa University, from which she graduated cum laude in April 2017. In 2016, she was an Erasmus student at Université Catholique de Louvain, where she specialized in International and European human rights law. In the summer of the same year, she took part in Amnesty International’s Human Rights Action Camp in Lampedusa, where she furthered her understanding of the migration crisis currently facing Europe. Martina also represented her University in two editions of the European Human Rights Moot Court Competition. In the 5th edition her team was runners-up for the written submissions. Her mother tongue is Italian, but she is also fluent in English, French and Spanish. Martina is working as a legal expert at the Foundation within the European Strategic Litigation Programme.</p>', 'Martina Guarracino', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-martina-guarracino', '', '', '2017-07-26 09:47:25', '2017-07-26 09:47:25', '', 0, 'https://hrlfoundation.org/?post_type=dict_team&#038;p=737', 0, 'dict_team', '', 0),
